&lt;p class=&quot;normal&quot; style=&quot; margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: -17.0pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: -7.05pt; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: windowtext;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;M&#225;s tarde, la C&#225;bala de Safed se difundi&#243; por Egipto, Turqu&#237;a e Italia, y luego a otros centros jud&#237;os por toda la di&#225;spora.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;normal&quot; style=&quot; text-align: justify; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: -17.0pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: -7.05pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: windowtext;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;En los siglos XVII y XVIII, la C&#225;bala de Safed y &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;El libro del esplendor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt; (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Sefer ha-Zohar&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;) generaron un movimiento mesi&#225;nico denominado sabateanismo. En Europa Oriental impuls&#243; un movimiento especial conocido como Jasid&#250;t.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
